{
  "texts": [
    "This process enables a much more efficient use of the limited parameter budget and directly accounts for the evolving needs of the model during fine-tuning.",
    "Rank Evolution PatternsA consistent trend observed across all datasets is the characteristic evolution of ranks over the course of training.",
    "At the beginning, DRaFT-Q initializes adapters with a small rank (e.g., $r=4$) to minimize VRAM usage.",
    "As training progresses, some layers-particularly in the middle and upper parts of the transformer-show increased gradient activity, signaling that these layers are learning complex, task-specific representations.",
    "The allocator responds by incrementally increasing rank for these layers, while keeping the rest of the network lightweight."
  ]
}